  op.youtube_video_id,
  op.title,
  COUNT(vs.id) as segment_count,
  array_agg(vs.keyword_timestamp) as timestamps
FROM public.youtube_videos_operational op
LEFT JOIN public.video_segments vs ON vs.operational_video_id = op.id
WHERE op.full_description ~ '\d{1,2}:\d{2}' -- Has timestamps
GROUP BY op.youtube_video_id, op.title
HAVING COUNT(vs.id) = 1;
-- Expected: 0 results (all should have multiple segments)
-- Actual: Many results with single 00:00:00 segment
```

**Example:**
```
Video: AZhQJZAh3no
full_description contains 7 timestamps:
  00:00 Programstart
  22:43 Robins intervjuer med landslaget
  43:01 Erik Flataker
  59:34 Reklampaus
  1:02:35 Noa Bachner
  1:48:18 Mattias BjÃ¤rsmyr
  2:00:05 Reklampaus
  
But only 1 segment created at 00:00:00
```

**Root Cause:** Phase 1 keyword filter was TOO STRICT:
- Checked if "AIK" appears in text after each timestamp
- Rejected ALL timestamps if no direct "AIK" mention
- Fell back to single 00:00:00 segment
- Video already validated at operational level, so keyword filter was redundant

**Status:** âœ… RESOLVED (2025-11-26)

**Fix Applied:**
1. Removed Phase 1 keyword filter (lines 310-317 in transform-videos/index.ts)
2. Videos already validated at operational level (language, sport, negative keywords)
3. Added sport-specific logic: Hockey 5+ timestamps â†’ 1 segment (Â§13.2.6)
4. Football/other sports: Create segments for ALL timestamps (max 20)

**New Behavior:**
- **Hockey** (5+ timestamps): Intentionally creates 1 segment at 00:00:00
- **Football** (any timestamps): Creates multiple segments, one per timestamp (max 20)
- **Other sports**: Follow football pattern

